title: Betrayal can be an inaccurately selfish frame.
pid: 3319db7f-b283-41ef-a849-c2bace4599de
body: |2-
  Betrayal is usually not motivated by hurting the victim, unless the betrayer is a sadist. And even in that unlikely case, they're probably more interested in the outcome for themselves than the effect of betrayal on the victim.
misc:
